<h2 id="orgbd5a1a0"><span class="section-number-2">3</span> Bearly Homework!:</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-3">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org8e760dd" class="outline-3 learn">
<h3 id="org8e760dd">Learn It</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org8e760dd">
<p>
<i>I feel like we're going in circles!</i>
</p>

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Let's learn about circles!</li>

<li>The Turtle library has a built-in function for making a circle!</li>
<li>We can call this function by typing turtle.circle()</li>
<li>Circles are a very useful tool!</li>
<li>Look at the example below for more tips on how to draw circles</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org2d4bc8c" class="outline-3 try">
<h3 id="org2d4bc8c">Try It</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org2d4bc8c">
<p>
<i>Think it, Trinket!</i>
</p>

<div class="HTML">
<p>
&lt;iframe src="<a href="https://trinket.io/embed/python/fd97e2dc6b">https://trinket.io/embed/python/fd97e2dc6b</a>" width="100%" 
height="600" frameborder="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
</p>

</div>

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Try editing the code to draw another smaller circle underneath (75)</li>
<li>Remember which direction to face to draw the circle downwards!</li>
<li>Try drawing another small circle in the middle of the bigger ones</li>
<li>Remember to use penup() and pendown() to move without drawing a line!</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org15f7d18" class="outline-3 code">
<h3 id="org15f7d18">Code It</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org15f7d18">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Now that you've mastered that, how about using this to draw some faces!</li>
<li>See if you can create a bear face like the one I created below!</li>
<li>Remember to use the:</li>
</ul>

<p>
1 Circle function (with radius and extent)
2 Triangle function that you made in previous lessons
3 The turtle.penup() and turtle.pendown() functions
</p>

<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Tip: Create a new function called DrawABear(): and put the code in there!</li>
</ul>


